          Read an article on Abendzeitung-Muenchen's web page that mentioned a cold has run through the Bayern squad. I told the courier "severe virus" so they are out til mid-March, but you get what you pay for. Lewandowski and Robben are back in training with the rest of the squad (as of yesterday/Monday) but Martinez, Vidal and Ulreich trained separately. Martinez was another with a cold, Vidal has a rib injury and Ulreich a hair gel-related issue, no doubt. Thiago picked up a knock in training, Coman is still out (as far as I know) and Boateng has realistically another 3 or 4 weeks to go (including rehab) til he is back after undergoing surgery last month. Being at home and after the winter break, Freiburg could score but if Lewa plays then he may score himself, it has been known. I'll predict 3-1 Bayern.
